messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/products/{id}

Method support (based on the code in routes/productRoutes.js):
- All HTTP methods acceptable? No
- HEAD: No (no explicit HEAD handler for /api/products/{id} in code)
- POST: No
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: Yes
- PUT: Yes
- DELETE: Yes
- PATCH: No

Explanation:
- The updateProduct handler is registered on the route /api/products/:id as part of the router in routes/productRoutes.js:
  - .get(checkObjectId, getProductById)
  - .put(protect, admin, checkObjectId, updateProduct)
  - .delete(protect, admin, checkObjectId, deleteProduct)
- The server mounts these routes under the /api/products prefix in server.js, so the full path for the update operation is /api/products/{id}.
- Therefore, for /api/products/{id}, the code explicitly supports GET, PUT, and DELETE. There are no explicit handlers for POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, or HEAD in the code. HEAD is not explicitly defined, though some servers may handle it automatically for GET, but since we are basing only on the code provided, we mark HEAD as not explicitly acceptable.
